{
  "texts": [
    "In specific, LLM+P [57] first transforms the task descriptions into formal Planning Domain Definition Languages (PDDL), and then it uses an external planner to deal with the PDDL.",
    "Finally, the generated results are transformed back into natural language by LLMs.",
    "Similarly, LLM-DP [58] utilizes LLMs to convert the observations, the current world state, and the target objectives into PDDL.",
    "Subsequently, this transformed data is passed to an external planner, which efficiently determines the final action sequence.",
    "CO-LLM [22] demonstrates that LLMs is good at generating high-level plans, but struggle with lowlevel control."
  ]
}